 id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>θ´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2018-09-11\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐκαρπί\n                    α\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐκαρπί\n                    α\">ΕΥΚΑ[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Α\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΧΡΗΣ.[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΙΡΕΕΖΗΣ[..]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΕΤΗ&nbsp;&nbsp;[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>Θ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001853_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-03-15\" src=\"ISic001853_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001853.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-03-15\" src=\"ISic001853-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Orsi: Ευκ[λειδ...]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Trace of the vertical of the Τ visible at line end\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Orsi: ἔζησ[εν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Orsi: Θ(εοῖς) [Κ(αταγαίοις)]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Farewell, worthy Eukarpia, you lived 8 years.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Two instances of the name Eukarpia are already attested at Centuripe (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000700\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000700\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004363\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004363\u003C/a>), and since it is clear from lines 2-3 that only 2-3 letters are missing on the right side, and with the Α preserved at the start of line 2, Eukarpia is almost the only plausible restoration. Given that a vacat is visible after ἔτη in line 4, and that the numeral θ (8) is would be complete for an age in years, and the layout is somewhat erratic, it is plausible that there are in fact no letters missing from the rest of lines 4 and 5. Alternatively, there might be a low age in years (single digit) followed by μῆνες (presumably abbreviated, e.g. μῆ(νες), followed then by the preserved numeral on line 5, in turn possibly followed by ἡμέρας (also abbreviated) and another numeral. \u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1915 231 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Somewhat crudely cut, plain letters of irregular size and without serifs. Lunate epsilon and sigma.\u003C/p> Line 1  29-35  Line 2  27-36  Line 3  26-34  Line 4  30  Line 5  27  Interlineation line 1 to 2  2-7  Interlineation line 2 to 3  4-7  Interlineation line 3 to 4  6  Interlineation line 4 to 5  6  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[230,233,236,239,242,245,248,251],{"id":231,"html":232},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2018-09-11\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐκαρπί\n                    α\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐκαρπί\n                    α\">Εὐκα[ρπί] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>α\u003C/span>\u003C/span> χρηστ̣[ά χα-]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ῖρε ἔζησ[ας] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ἔτη \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>θ´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2018-09-11\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐκαρπί\n                    α\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐκαρπί\n                    α\">ΕΥΚΑ[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Α\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΧΡΗΣ.[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΙΡΕΕΖΗΣ[..]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΕΤΗ&nbsp;&nbsp;[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>Θ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":234,"html":235},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001853_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-03-15\" src=\"ISic001853_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001853.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-03-15\" src=\"ISic001853-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":237,"html":238},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Orsi: Ευκ[λειδ...]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Trace of the vertical of the Τ visible at line end\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Orsi: ἔζησ[εν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Orsi: Θ(εοῖς) [Κ(αταγαίοις)]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":240,"html":241},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Farewell, worthy Eukarpia, you lived 8 years.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":243,"html":244},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Two instances of the name Eukarpia are already attested at Centuripe (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000700\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000700\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004363\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004363\u003C/a>), and since it is clear from lines 2-3 that only 2-3 letters are missing on the right side, and with the Α preserved at the start of line 2, Eukarpia is almost the only plausible restoration. Given that a vacat is visible after ἔτη in line 4, and that the numeral θ (8) is would be complete for an age in years, and the layout is somewhat erratic, it is plausible that there are in fact no letters missing from the rest of lines 4 and 5. Alternatively, there might be a low age in years (single digit) followed by μῆνες (presumably abbreviated, e.g. μῆ(νες), followed then by the preserved numeral on line 5, in turn possibly followed by ἡμέρας (also abbreviated) and another numeral. \u003C/p>  ",{"id":246,"html":247},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1915 231 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":249,"html":250},"handnote","\u003Cp>Somewhat crudely cut, plain letters of irregular size and without serifs. Lunate epsilon and sigma.\u003C/p> Line 1  29-35  Line 2  27-36  Line 3  26-34  Line 4  30  Line 5  27  Interlineation line 1 to 2  2-7  Interlineati